Italia 2004</copyright-statement></permissions><abstract id="Abs1"><p>Placebo and placebo effect are important issues related to the drug therapy for clinical and scientific meanings. The rates of placebo may get as many as 50% for analgesic drugs in headache. The high answer to placebo brings questions on pathophysiology of headache. Answers may offer a new strategy in the implementation of trials and new insight in neurophysiology of headache. Current knowledge on placebo and placebo effect will be analysed and dicussed looking for new direction in headache field.</p></abstract><kwd-group xml:lang="en"><title><bold>Key words</bold></title><kwd>Placebo</kwd><kwd>Headache</kwd><kwd>Migraine</kwd><kwd>Treatment</kwd><kwd>Drug therapy</kwd></kwd-group><custom-meta-group><custom-meta><meta-name>issue-copyright-statement</meta-name><meta-value>&#x000a9; Springer-Verlag
